  "texts": [
    "The ResNet50 architecture was slightly modified by freezing the upper layers and fine-tuning the lower layers with the fossil-specific data, improving its ability to accurately classify bone modifications.",
    "The modifications primarily enhanced the model's precision in identifying subtle differences between marks that are often difficult to distinguish, but is critical for the accurate interpretation of the site's taphonomic history.",
    "The study did, however, rely on high-quality, controlled experimental data for training, and this may not fully represent the variability and degradation present in the actual archaeological record.",
    "Lastly, Domínguez-Rodrigo et al. (2023) present a robust DL framework utilizing TL and ensemble methods to differentiate between tribes of African bovids (cloven-hoofed ruminants, a group including 1 3 cattle).",
    "The architectural novelty lies in the combination of multiple pre-trained models, such as ResNet-50, DenseNet-201, EfficientNet-B7, and VGG19, with ensemble learning to enhance predictive performance, particularly in identifying the nuanced differences in the occlusal (biting) surfaces of teeth."
